      "source": [
        "## 9. Using `super()` in Multiple Inheritance\n",
        "\n",
        "`super()` is particularly important in multiple inheritance to ensure that methods are called in the correct order according to the MRO. When a method is called using `super()`, Python looks for the next class in the MRO after the current class and calls that class's version of the method. This enables cooperative multiple inheritance.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Example 9: Using `super()` with Multiple Inheritance and Overlapping Methods**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "9dc72c63",
        "outputId": "adf2eb73-fde4-45ed-b1bf-4658efad7bce"
      },
      "source": [
        "class A:\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from A\")\n",
        "        # Using super() here is crucial for cooperative inheritance\n",
        "        # Call the method from the next class in the MRO\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class B:\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from B\")\n",
        "        # Using super() here is crucial for cooperative inheritance\n",
        "        # Call the method from the next class in the MRO\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class C(A, B): # C inherits from A then B\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from C\")\n",
        "        # super() will call the next method in the MRO (A's method)\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class D(B, A): # D inherits from B then A (different MRO)\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from D\")\n",
        "        # super() will call the next method in the MRO (B's method)\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "# To make the super().method() calls work correctly in the hierarchy,\n",
        "# the base class in the MRO (ultimately 'object') must also have a method that\n",
        "# is called by super(). In this case, the 'object' class does not have a 'method'.\n",
        "# A common pattern is to have a base class that finishes the super() chain,\n",
        "# or to ensure all classes in the MRO have the method being called.\n",
        "# For this example to run without AttributeError at the end of the chain,\n",
        "# we can add a method to a common base class or modify the classes.\n",
        "# A simpler fix for demonstration is to catch the AttributeError or\n",
        "# ensure the chain ends gracefully. However, the intended behavior with super()\n",
        "# in cooperative multiple inheritance is for the calls to continue up the MRO.\n",
        "# The original code demonstrates the *intended* flow, but hits the limit\n",
        "# when 'object' is reached and doesn't have 'method'.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Let's add a base class that completes the chain gracefully.\n",
        "class BaseCompleter:\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        # This method exists to be called by super() when the end of the\n",
        "        # intended hierarchy is reached before 'object'.\n",
        "        print(\"Method from BaseCompleter (ending the chain)\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class A_fixed(BaseCompleter):\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from A_fixed\")\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class B_fixed(BaseCompleter):\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from B_fixed\")\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class C_fixed(A_fixed, B_fixed): # C inherits from A then B\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from C_fixed\")\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "class D_fixed(B_fixed, A_fixed): # D inherits from B then A (different MRO)\n",
        "    def method(self):\n",
        "        print(\"Method from D_fixed\")\n",
        "        super().method()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create instances and call the method\n",
        "print(\"Calling method on C_fixed instance:\")\n",
        "c_instance_fixed = C_fixed()\n",
        "c_instance_fixed.method()\n",
        "print(\"\\nMRO for C_fixed:\")\n",
        "print(C_fixed.__mro__)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nCalling method on D_fixed instance:\")\n",
        "d_instance_fixed = D_fixed()\n",
        "d_instance_fixed.method()\n",
        "print(\"\\nMRO for D_fixed:\")\n",
        "print(D_fixed.__mro__)"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Calling method on C_fixed instance:\n",
            "Method from C_fixed\n",
            "Method from A_fixed\n",
            "Method from B_fixed\n",
            "Method from BaseCompleter (ending the chain)\n",
            "\n",
            "MRO for C_fixed:\n",
            "(<class '__main__.C_fixed'>, <class '__main__.A_fixed'>, <class '__main__.B_fixed'>, <class '__main__.BaseCompleter'>, <class 'object'>)\n",
            "\n",
            "Calling method on D_fixed instance:\n",
            "Method from D_fixed\n",
            "Method from B_fixed\n",
            "Method from A_fixed\n",
            "Method from BaseCompleter (ending the chain)\n",
            "\n",
            "MRO for D_fixed:\n",
            "(<class '__main__.D_fixed'>, <class '__main__.B_fixed'>, <class '__main__.A_fixed'>, <class '__main__.BaseCompleter'>, <class 'object'>)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "04b116f8"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Explanation:**\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Classes `A` and `B` both have a `method` that calls `super().method()`.\n",
        "*   Class `C` inherits from `A` then `B`. Its MRO is `[C, A, B, object]`. When `c_instance.method()` is called, `C.method()` runs, then `super().method()` in `C` calls `A.method()`, then `super().method()` in `A` calls `B.method()`, and finally `super().method()` in `B` calls `object.method()` (which does nothing).\n",
        "*   Class `D` inherits from `B` then `A`. Its MRO is `[D, B, A, object]`. When `d_instance.method()` is called, `D.method()` runs, then `super().method()` in `D` calls `B.method()`, then `super().method()` in `B` calls `A.method()`, and finally `super().method()` in `A` calls `object.method()`.\n",
        "*   This clearly shows how `super()` follows the MRO to determine which method to call next in the inheritance chain."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "54c5f411"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 10. More Advanced Examples and Use Cases\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's explore some more advanced scenarios and demonstrate other potential uses of `super()`.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Example 10: Using `super()` with Class Methods**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "e91a8574",
        "outputId": "972ffc45-e44f-468b-f21d-9e9141593957"
      },
      "source": [
        "class Base:\n",
        "    @classmethod\n",
        "    def class_info(cls):\n",
        "        print(f\"This is a class method from Base class: {cls.__name__}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class Derived(Base):\n",
        "    @classmethod\n",
        "    def class_info(cls):\n",
        "        print(f\"This is a class method from Derived class: {cls.__name__}\")\n",
        "        # Call the parent class method using super()\n",
        "        super().class_info()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Call the class method on the derived class\n",
        "Derived.class_info()"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "This is a class method from Derived class: Derived\n",
            "This is a class method from Base class: Derived\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ca97a5a3"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Explanation:**\n",
        "\n",
        "*   `super()` can be used within class methods (`@classmethod`) to call the parent class's class method.\n",
        "*   `super().class_info()` in `Derived` calls the `class_info` method from the `Base` class."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0e0c8532"
