        "**Example 12: Abstract Base Classes and Inheritance (Advanced Concept)**\n",
        "\n",
        "Inheritance is often used with Abstract Base Classes (ABCs) to define interfaces that subclasses must implement. The `abc` module in Python helps with this."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
